OK, OK. So, yeah, so I was saying that it's also very important to provide feedback to your users.

00:17:59.560 --> 00:18:07.439
This is. You don't want your users to know that.

00:18:07.439 --> 00:18:13.119
Your app, you want you want users to to be aware of what's happening with the app.

00:18:13.119 --> 00:18:19.640
This this usually means using progress bars, using messages, using notifications.

00:18:19.640 --> 00:18:28.719
You should always provide some kind of feedback to make sure that your users don't get lost or are waiting for some very long process,

00:18:28.719 --> 00:18:32.719
some very long script that's running and they have no idea what's happening.

00:18:32.719 --> 00:18:39.479
If if you have something that you know is going to take more than a few seconds, odds are the progress bar.

00:18:39.479 --> 00:18:46.719
If you have something that can be done in the background while your user is using the application,

00:18:46.760 --> 00:18:53.079
make it maybe show a notification when when when it's over.

00:18:53.079 --> 00:18:58.599
All of this constant feedback really helps when it comes to the user experience.

00:18:58.599 --> 00:19:08.319
And finally, remember to think about the default values. Shiny dashboards live of inputs of user user inputs.

00:19:08.319 --> 00:19:15.439
And a lot of the times these inputs can be defaulted to some values that are very common for users to use.

00:19:15.439 --> 00:19:23.439
If you have a drop down, but you know that's most commonly this is the value that's used are the value to that drop down or preselect the drop down.

00:19:23.439 --> 00:19:27.719
If you have a checkbox that most of the time is selected, selected by default,

00:19:27.719 --> 00:19:36.599
anything that's avoids unnecessary actions by the user and can make the experience much faster and much smoother.

